How to Make a Discord Bot in Python

What You’ll Need;

1. Python 3.10+ (install from python.org, check “Add Python to PATH” during setup)
2. VS Code (with the Microsoft Python extension)
3. Discord Developer Portal account (to create your bot and get its token)
4. Hosting method:
  Self‑hosting (bot runs only while your PC is on)
  Cloud hosting (Replit, Railway, VPS) for 24/7 uptime

Below is a simple, complete, beginner-friendly guide on how to make a Discord bot in Python, using the requirements listed. I’ll show you step-by-step how to create the bot, write the code, run it, and invite it to your server.

🛠 Step‑By‑Step Setup

step 1. create a folder on you desktop called my discord bot then open it in vs code.

step 2. then create 2 files one called "bot.py" and one called ".env".
          Project Folder:
            My discord bot/
                  bot.py
                  .env

step 3. now copy my versions of bot.py and .env into your files you have just created.

step 4. then go to the discord developer portal (https://discord.com/developers/)
1. Create Your Bot in the Developer Portal:

  Go to Discord Developer Portal

  Click New Application → name it

  In Bot tab click reset bot token (For security purposes, tokens can only be viewed once, when created. If you forgot or lost access to your token, please regenerate a new one.)

  Then Copy your Bot Token (⚠ keep it secret, like a password) and paste it into your .env file after "DISCORD_TOKEN=" make sure you delete "YOUR_BOT_TOKEN_HERE" and add your bot token

  In Bot tab → Add Bot

  Enable MESSAGE CONTENT INTENT (others optional)

3. Install Dependencies
  bash
  pip install discord.py python-dotenv

4. then copy .env (create a file called .env and copy my version included)

5. then copy bot.py (create a file called bot.py and copy my version included)

6. Run Your Bot
  bash
  python bot.py

If successful:
  Code
  ✅ Logged in as <botname>

7. Invite Bot to Your Server
  Developer Portal → OAuth2 → URL Generator

  Scopes: bot, applications.commands

  Permissions: Send Messages, Use Slash Commands (add more if needed)

  Copy URL → paste in browser → select server → Authorize
